'''Bristol Bach Choir''' is an auditioned amateur choir based in [[Bristol]].

== Conductors ==

*[[Adrian Beaumont]] 1967<U+2013>1978
*Alistair Jones 1978<U+2013>1982
*Glyn Jenkins 1982<U+2013>1999
*Peter Leech 1999<U+2013>2008
*[[Gavin Carr]] 2009<U+2013>2011

[http://wellensian-consort.co.uk/musical-director Christopher Finch] 2012

== History ==
The choir was founded in 1966 by [[University of Bristol]] colleagues Alan Farnill and [[Adrian Beaumont]].

